  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Write vertex form using vertex $(2, 5)$",
      "content": "$$f(x) = a(x-2)^2 + 5$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve for $a$ using point $(3, 42)$",
      "content": "$$42 = a(3-2)^2 + 5 \\implies a = 37$$<br/>So $f(x) = 37(x-2)^2 + 5$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Compute $f(-1) - f(1)$",
      "content": "$$f(-1) = 37(-3)^2 + 5 = 333 + 5 = 338$$<br/>$$f(1) = 37(-1)^2 + 5 = 37 + 5 = 42$$<br/>$$f(-1) - f(1) = 338 - 42 = 296$$<br/>That is the correct answer."
    }
  ]
}